print

print.pumping_test.Rd

Function to print on the screen a pumping_test object

\method{print}{pumping_test}(x, ...)

Arguments

x

A pumping_test object
...

Additional parameters to the data.frame print function

Value

This function prints the information from the pumping test on the screen

See also

Other base functions: additional.parameters<-, confint.pumping_test, confint_bootstrap, confint_jackniffe, confint_wald, estimated<-, evaluate, fit.optimization, fit.parameters<-, fit.sampling, fit, hydraulic.parameter.names<-, hydraulic.parameters<-, model.parameters, model<-, plot.pumping_test, plot_model_diagnostic, pumping_test, simulate, summary.pumping_test

Examples

# Define a pumping test
tt <- logseq(0, 5, 30)
Tr <- 1e-3
Ss <- 0.0001
r <- 1e3
Q <- 1e-3
s <- Q/(4*pi*Tr)*theis_well_function(tt)
ptest <- pumping_test("Test", Q = Q, r = r, t = tt, s = s)
print(ptest)
